Polish Potato, Kielbasa, and Cabbage Soup (Kapusniak)

**blatantly stolen from Kenji's Serious Eats recipe**

https://www.seriouseats.com/polish-potato-kielbasa-cabbage-soup-kapusniak-recipe

  - 6 oz bacon, cut into lardons
  - 12 oz kielbasa, cut into bite sized rounds
  - 1 onion, sliced
  - 2-3 carrots, faux tourne
  - 0.5 head cabbage
  - 8 oz sauerkraut
  - 2 quarts chicken stock
  - 2 bay leaves
  - 0.25 cups dill, chopped, stems reserved
  - 1 large russet potato
  - 2 tsp paprika
  - optional: crusty bread

  (1) crisp up bacon in a large dutch oven
  (2) add kielbasa, cook until browning somewhat
  (3) add paprika, frying in rendered fat until fragrant
  (3) add onion & carrot, cook until softened somewhat
  (4) add cabbage & cook until wilted
  (5) add sauerkraut, chicken stock, bay leaves, dill stems, and potato, season to taste
  (6) bring to simmer, cook for 15 min
  (7) serve w sprinkled dill & bread
